8:
...It's no use. I bet the damage wasn't 
contained to just this floor.
11:
It seemed like a regular shift, but 
I never expected the whole pathway to 
crumble.
15:
Do you think it's because I've been 
blasting tunnels everywhere?
18: It is not your fault, Clarisse.
21:
Yeah, what Stella said. The 
Kaleidoscope repairs itself super fast, 
so this couldn't have been you.
23:
But, uh, why don't you just blast our 
way out now?
26:
Mm... I could, but we might get caught 
in the kapow?
29:
Perhaps we should try after finding 
a more stable location. Our current 
area is not safe for such 
experimentation.
33:
Let's just wait for a rescue team. I'm 
sure someone will come soon.
42: Are you guys really okay with this?
46:
Eh, we're used to getting into sticky 
situations.
49:
Yes. Though it is much more 
entertaining with your presence, 
Clarisse.
53:
Whoa, what happened? Were you guys 
thrown in prison somewhere?
57:
We didn't tell you? At first, we were 
both trapped in Starview Village.
60:
Oh yeeeah! You said you had amnesia, 
right?
63:
Yep. I don't remember anything before 
waking up in the village.
70:
Nothing. But that's okay. Stella's in the 
same boat, right?
74: Yes. I am not sure who my parents are.
82:
What about you, Clarisse? Do you 
have family?
85: We would love to hear about them.
89:
Really? My family's nothing special 
though. Let's see...
91:
My parents once ordered me to kill 
Master—er, who's basically my 
ancestor.
99:
Don't get the wrong idea! I mean, yeah, 
we've had our moments...
101:
But the whole family is fine now. Mom 
and Dad and me finally learned how to 
talk to each other.
105:
Though it sure helps that I became the 
head of the family! We've got zero 
problems with me in charge!
108:
YOU'RE the head? Man, family's come 
in all shapes and sizes, huh?
110:
Can't help but be a little envious 
though.
114: You want to find your family?
117:
Umm... I'm not sure how that would 
go. I probably hail from some boring 
old town.
121: Well, I wouldn't mind meeting them.
123:
In fact, I know they're good people! 
I bet you've got older siblings! Your big 
brother or sister are going to be great!
130:
I mean YOU'RE not the big brother 
type. Right, Stella?
137: Heeey, what's that supposed to mean?
141: Huh? I, I don't feel so good...
150: Wait, I'm start, starting to feel faint too.
154:
Miasma has been known to escape 
from underground pockets.
158:
For real? Stupid poison gas... Alk! 
Hang in there!
167:
Oh no, are we all gonna bite the big 
one?
170: No! NO! Not on my watch!
173:
This wall should do the trick. I can't 
make fire; not enough space for a big 
impact... If I can just use dissolution…
175:
But the kapow might swallow us all—
not a good look...
185:
Yeah... Yeah! I believe in me too! All 
I have to do is give it a little backbone!
194: Yay! Wait... This doesn't look right!
202: Aaah! If, if you say so! Here we go, Alk!
214:
Phew... You're amazing. What did you 
do exactly?
222:
Um, well... I did a little of this, and 
a little of that!
226:
Wait a minute. How come it didn't 
work this time?
229:
Haha. Maybe you work better under 
pressure. You saved our bacon 
regardless.
232:
Indeed. Thanks to you, we have 
returned safe and sound.
237:
Hooray, me! Hooray, alchemy! It got 
us back home, sweet home!
